The paper deals with the task of neural associative memory, which is a subfield of neural networks and machine learning. The use of convolutional neural networks and iterative algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. The focus on maximizing pattern retrieval capacity and maintaining reliability suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The use of natural patterns such as images suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The use of redundancy among patterns suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of iterative algorithms and the focus on reliability suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
